    "cooking_instructions": [
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 220\u00b0C/ 200\u00b0C (fan)/ gas 7 and boil a kettle, then take your <strong>chicken</strong> out of the fridge, open the packet and let it air</p><p>Chop your<strong> leek[s] </strong>into rounds and wash thoroughly to remove any grit, then slice your <strong>potatoes</strong> (skins on) into thin discs</p><p>Add the <strong>sliced potato</strong> and <strong>leek</strong> <strong>rounds</strong> to a pot of plenty of<strong> boiled water</strong>, bring to the boil over a high heat and cook for 5-6 min or until softened slightly</p>",
            "order": 1,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-1.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Once the veg has softened slightly, drain it and transfer to an <strong>oven-proof dish</strong> (save the pot!)</p><p>Meanwhile, melt 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [40g]</span> <strong>butter </strong>in the reserved pot over a medium heat</p><p>Once melted, add 20g<span class=\"text-purple\"> [30g]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[40g]</span> <strong>flour</strong> and stir with a wooden spoon for 1 min or until a sandy paste forms \u2013 this is your <strong>roux</strong></p><p>Add 250ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[375ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[500ml]</span> <strong>milk </strong>gradually and whisk for 5 min or until a smooth, thick sauce remains \u2013 this is your <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong></p>",
            "order": 2,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-2.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Remove the <strong>b\u00e9chamel sauce</strong> from the heat, season with a grind of <strong>black</strong> <strong>pepper</strong> and stir through <strong>half</strong> your <strong>grated Italian hard</strong> <strong>cheese </strong>and<strong> Dijon mustard </strong>\u2013 this is your<strong> cheesy b\u00e9chamel</strong></p><p>Pour the <strong>cheesy b\u00e9chamel</strong> over the leek & potato and top with the <strong>remaining</strong> <strong>grated Italian hard cheese</strong>, reserve the pot</p><p>Cook for 30-35 min or until the potato is cooked through and the top is golden \u2013 this is your <strong>creamy potato & leek gratin</strong></p>",
            "order": 3,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-3.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Whilst the gratin is cooking, wrap your <strong>chicken breast portion[s]</strong> in your <strong>smoked streaky bacon</strong>, then transfer to a <strong>baking paper</strong>-lined tray</p><p>Put the tray in the oven for 25-30 min or until the chicken is cooked through (no pink meat!) and the bacon is slightly crispy \u2013 this is your <strong>chicken</strong> <strong>wrapped in bacon</strong></p>",
            "order": 4,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-4.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Reboil half a kettle</p><p>Peel and finely slice your <strong>shallot[s]</strong></p><p>Peel and finely chop (or grate!) your <strong>garlic</strong></p><p>Return the reserved pot to a medium-high heat with a generous drizzle of <strong>olive oil </strong>and once hot, add the <strong>chopped shallot</strong> and cook for 1-2 min or until softened</p>",
            "order": 5,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-5.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Dissolve your <strong>chicken stock mix</strong> in 175ml <span class=\"text-purple\">[230ml]</span> <span class=\"text-danger\">[300ml]</span> <strong>boiled water</strong></p><p>Once softened, add the <strong>chopped garlic</strong> to the pot along with 1 tsp <span class=\"text-purple\">[1 1/2 tsp]</span><span class=\"text-danger\"> [2 tsp]</span> <strong>flour </strong>and cook for 30 secs</p><p>Add the <strong>chicken stock</strong> to the pot and cook for 5-6 min or until reduced to a gravy-like consistency \u2013 this is your <strong>gravy</strong></p>",
            "order": 6,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-6.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a knob of <strong>butter</strong> over a medium heat</p><p>Wash your <strong>shredded kale</strong> </p><p>Once hot, add the <strong>shredded kale</strong> and <strong>blanched peas</strong> and cook for 3-4 min or until tender with a bite \u2013 these are your <strong>buttery greens</strong></p>",
            "order": 7,
            "image": "/images/instructions/chicken-wrapped-in-bacon-with-creamy-potato-and-leek-gratin/step-7.jpg"
        },
        {
            "instruction": "<p>Serve the<strong> chicken</strong> <strong>wrapped in bacon </strong>with the <strong>creamy potato & leek gratin</strong> and <strong>buttery greens</strong> to the side</p><p>Enjoy!</p>",
            "order": 8
        }
    ],
